Author: flatrick
Title: 🔥[ANN][Live ICO] 🔥Efir.io - P2P “AdWords” for native advertising with bloggers
Body: Thx for a good question. Yes we focus only on bloggers. Bloggers focus gives us an opportunity to make the best bloggers platform.  Blogger is a specialist. Platform doesn't matter. It could be text, audio or video content-platform. But not all social nets allow p2p advertising. Social networks are not interested in developing p2p advertising market as advertiser’s money goes directly to bloggers leaving out the social nets. Some Social networks have an opportunity to fight p2p market, but others can’t do anything. All social networks can be divided into two segments – communication oriented (Facebook, Instagram,...) and content oriented (YouTube, Twitch, Youku…). Communication oriented networks are mostly used for communication among friends. Such social networks camouflage advertising in posts and are not interested in supporting blogger’s activity which leads to an obvious limitation for bloggers and advertising with them. For instance, Facebook does not allow having more than 5000 friends. Instagram bans links to external sources. Content oriented networks are normally used for unique content. The main instrument for accessing the content is subscription to particular bloggers but this way requires following the social network’s instructions. Special competences and resources are necessary to generate high quality content. Being a part of such networks becomes a regular job for popular creators (bloggers). Normally, there is a high volume of content and the user needs time to check every post, so the network integrates advertising into this content. Such social networks cannot exist without bloggers. Therefore they are interested in opinion leaders’ development. It is useless for content oriented (Youtube, Twitch and so on) networks to fight p2p advertising. Any kind of pressure exerted on bloggers harms the audience. In such situation, content oriented networks can’t do anything to decrease p2p advertising market. So Youtube as the biggest content-oriented social network is our priority. Instagram, Facebook and others are not.

Try it here https://efir.io/youtube  We are implementing systemically significant subprojects to break market barriers. Ex: agencies.efir.io, prquality.efir.io, analytics.efir.io, Production.efir.io and published. We are developing open API to integrate external startups to our ecosystem. All the subprojects we develop and integrate use QZ token. So every deal on every subproject should increase the token value. Every new external subproject should increase the token value.  Whatever you do on bloggers market, it's coneinient to use our ecosystem to develop. So just using efir.io you increase the token value.

Author: Shivraj Singh
Title: 🔥[ANN][Live ICO] 🔥Efir.io - P2P “AdWords” for native advertising with bloggers
Body: Great project..... congratulations....team plan Blogger is a specialist. Platform doesn't matter. It could be text, audio or video content-platform. But not all social nets allow p2p advertising. Social networks are not interested in developing p2p advertising market as advertiser’s money goes directly to bloggers leaving out the social nets. Some Social networks have an opportunity to fight p2p market, but others can’t do anything. All social networks can be divided into two segments – communication oriented (Facebook, Instagram,...) and content oriented (YouTube, Twitch, Youku…). Communication oriented networks are mostly used for communication among friends. Such social networks camouflage advertising in posts and are not interested in supporting blogger’s activity which leads to an obvious limitation for bloggers and advertising with them. For instance, Facebook does not allow having more than 5000 friends. Instagram bans links to external sources. Content oriented networks are normally used for unique content. The main instrument for accessing the content is subscription to particular bloggers but this way requires following the social network’s instructions. Special competences and resources are necessary to generate high quality content. Being a part of such networks becomes a regular job for popular creators (bloggers). Normally, there is a high volume of content and the user needs time to check every post, so the network integrates advertising into this content. Such social networks cannot exist without bloggers. Therefore they are interested in opinion leaders’ development. It is useless for content oriented (Youtube, Twitch and so on) networks to fight p2p advertising. Any kind of pressure exerted on bloggers harms the audience. In such situation, content oriented networks can’t do anything to decrease p2p advertising market. So Youtube as the biggest content-oriented social network is our priority. Instagram, Facebook and others are not.

Author: qaazqaaz
Title: 🔥[ANN][Live ICO] 🔥Efir.io - P2P “AdWords” for native advertising with bloggers
Body: Important announcement  We haven’t launched all the activities planned for the main token sale stage. That’s why we extend it to the 31 of July. I am making this decision in order to protect  investments of all investors who have already joined the sale. It doesn’t cause the change in implementation of the project.  We are developing Efir.io and launching projects in its ecosystem. In June analytics.efir.io will start working internationally.  At the moment is works only on a Russia segment.  With analytics.efir.io you will know what your audience is talking about. Very soon we will add about 30 000 bloggers with at least 20 000 subscribers each.  Therefore, through our search it will be possible to find the majority of Youtubers.  In July we are planning to start openly testing the service of generation the smart-contracts between bloggers and advertisers.  Hence right after the end of token sale we will be able to do first smart-contract deals. Be with us. We will change the market to the better together.  Sincerely yours, Denis Shaiakhmetov Founder and Owner Efir.io

Author: qaazqaaz
Title: 🔥[ANN][Live ICO] 🔥Efir.io - P2P “AdWords” for native advertising with bloggers
Body: Yes, we focus only on bloggers ad, as bloggers could easily make native ad. Native ad is a future of advertising.   Text, Video, Audio - it doesn't matter. The platform is important. All social networks can be divided into two segments – communication oriented (Facebook, Instagram,...) and content oriented (YouTube, Twitch, …). Communication oriented networks are mostly used for communication among friends. Such social networks camouflage advertising in posts and are not interested in supporting blogger’s activity which leads to an obvious limitation for bloggers and advertising with them. For instance, Facebook does not allow having more than 5000 friends. Instagram bans links to external sources.  Content oriented networks are normally used for unique content. The main instrument for accessing the content is subscription to particular bloggers but this way requires following the social network’s instructions. Special competences and resources are necessary to generate high quality content. Being a part of such networks becomes a regular job for popular creators (bloggers). Normally, there is a high volume of content and the user needs time to check every post, so the network integrates advertising into this content. Such social networks cannot exist without bloggers. Therefore they are interested in opinion leaders’ development. It is useless for content oriented (Youtube, Twitch and so on) networks to fight p2p advertising. Any kind of pressure exerted on bloggers harms the audience. In such situation, content oriented networks can’t do anything to decrease p2p advertising market. So Youtube as the biggest content-oriented social network is our priority. Instagram, Facebook and others are not

Author: qaazqaaz
Title: 🔥[ANN][Live ICO] 🔥Efir.io - P2P “AdWords” for native advertising with bloggers
Body: In 2016 for one of our clients we started buying advertisement from Youtube bloggers. We have gotten fantastic results. However, to achieve them we had to go through hell and face the same problems all the time. The most difcult part was bloggers selection. Why are we developing Efir.io? New native advertisement market paradigm That was because there were no free search engines which provided bloggers’ price rates and contact details on the market. But the absence of search engines wasn’t the only problem that we had faced. The fact that bloggers aren’t professional advertisers hampers getting high quality native advertisement. Moreover, it’s impossible to pay bloggers according to the classic CPA model. That’s because that kind of advertisement is more about PR than actual sales. Advertising agencies don’t really help the market. First of all, there are not that many of them. Secondly, the existing ones are drowning in work. Moreover, generally, the market is opaque. In January of 2017, after collecting data of 300 bloggers (contact details and price rates), we openly and freely published our database and gave bloggers an opportunity to join.

Author: qaazqaaz
Title: 🔥[ANN][Live ICO] 🔥Efir.io - P2P “AdWords” for native advertising with bloggers
Body: Our service Analytics.efir.io will make the market transparent. As the market is P2P, it couldn't be controlled as usual.

Author: qaazqaaz
Title: 🔥[ANN][Live ICO] 🔥Efir.io - P2P “AdWords” for native advertising with bloggers
Body: Blockchain helps to connect international market players, for example, bloggers and advertisers from different countries. If an advertiser wants to work with an international blogger it’s possible to use QZs — Efir crypto currency. This will help to avoid paying commission for money transaction. And this applies to all the services. For example, bloggers can collaborate with media specialists from other countries, increase the quality of advertisement and satisfy advertisers who will come back to them over and over again. Besides, Blockchain helps to make the market more transparent as the external oracles monitor the deal and the recipient will get the payment only after all the conditions have been fulfilled. Efir can help advertisers avoid mistakes in working with bloggers and this will help native advertising market to develop further. However, its rapid and productive development is impossible without Blockchain technology which facilitates the financial side of the relationships between the international market players and brings true transparency to the opaque market of native advertising.

Author: qaazqaaz
Title: 🔥[ANN][Live ICO] 🔥Efir.io - P2P “AdWords” for native advertising with bloggers
Body: Lets talk about main platform. We launched efir.io in January of 2017 on a temporary domain qaazqaaz.com. During next 6 months every 4th top Russian speaking blogger joined efir.io. We invited bloggers by email. Business model and idea was so innovate and necessary for the market, so to reach 1/4 part of the CIS market we hadn't pay for advertising. In august 2017 we started foreign localization. By the end of march 2018 we have published intellectual search for 170 thousand youtube accounts from  all over the world. Bloggers' stats and contact details are opened for search engines so every advertiser looking for blogger gets only 1 platform in search. Try it. Google "Nastya Tropicelle advertising". So search engines is the best free promotion for us. To make our ICO successful, we have started promotion. So we have several articles for ex https://btcmanager.com/efir-io-tokenizes-advertising-with-bloggers/, https://themerkle.com/tokenization-of-multibillion-market-of-bloggers-advertising/. We have successful listings https://findico.io/ico/efirio-qz https://www.trackico.io/ico/efirio/#tab-rating https://icolink.com/ico-exchange-efir.html http://cryptoconsulting.info/ico-list/?ico=Efir https://icobench.com/ico/efir https://foundico.com/ru/ico/efir.html You could find reviews from popular bloggers, for ex Clif High https://www.halfpasthuman.com/

Title: 🔥[ANN][Live ICO] 🔥Efir.io - P2P “AdWords” for native advertising with bloggers
Body: Advertisers Select bloggers with intellectual search Set up the conditions for advertisement placement with help of external oracles Follow the statistics and get the results Pay in tokens while using oracles  Bloggers Publish price rates, contact details, statistics Answer offers of advertisers or look for tasks from brands themselves Increase the quality of content and advertisement while working in a team with media specialist May recieve payments in tokens  IT-services Join the platform through open API and make money selling services and oracles to the market players The deals are performed in tokens  Media-specialists Publish portfolio and offer bloggers workshops/lessons or partnership, assessing their content according to such competencies as editing, work with lighting, advertisement quality, etc  QZ-Investors Buy tokens on the stock Sale Sale them with other members of ecosystem by buying services from external market players, paying for bloggers advertising and performing international money transactions Profit on investments in bloggers development  Agencies Find advertisers and bloggers Sell their services Automate their business-processes

Author: qaazqaaz
Title: 🔥[ANN][Live ICO] 🔥Efir.io - P2P “AdWords” for native advertising with bloggers
Body: Absolutely. But not everyone will be a professional. We will help bloggers to become professional. What competencies should a blogger have to become a professional? Blogger has to be a cameraman, sound director, video editor, screenwriter, graphic designer and so on at the same time. We know 8 main and 40 secondary competencies of the professional blogger.  We gather media market specialists to professional associations and make the blogger go through this associations. First stage is bloggers assessment. As a result we get a professional team consisting of a blogger and a market media specialists. Specialists could teach the blogger or get employed as a part of the team. When the blogger’s team is formed, venture investor could buy the blogger’s rights for future advertisement placements. Third stage - bloggers development. Collected funds are used by blogger’s team to develop. It leads to rising of the content quality, audience growths and increase in blogger’s advertising cost. So the advertising rights held by investor become more expensive. The last stage - to sell advertising rights using efir.io. So every deal on decentralized production will increase the token value.

Author: qaazqaaz
Title: 🔥[ANN][Live ICO] 🔥Efir.io - P2P “AdWords” for native advertising with bloggers
Body: Bloggers register on the platform, provide their nonpublic statistics, contact details and price rates. We make bloggers accounts accessible to search engines. Advertisers look for the bloggers via Google where they get our accounts, or use our intellectual search. We can’t force all the youtubers register on the platform. So in the beginning, we publish bloggers accounts only with contact details and public data. It gives an advertiser an opportunity to easily find and directly connect with bloggers. If a blogger and an advertiser are in different countries and the audience matches, it’s convenient to use our smart-contract to avoid paying commissions. Moreover, smart-contract oracles could help an advertiser to pay for the measurable result of advertising and not for the fact of it. An advertiser could choose one of the multiple alternative external oracles. Vast choice of external oracles will make them cheaper for advertiser. This approach leads the market to classic CPA model.

Author: qaazqaaz
Title: 🔥[ANN][Live ICO] 🔥Efir.io - P2P “AdWords” for native advertising with bloggers
Body: Yes, we focus only on bloggers ad, as bloggers could easily make native ad. Native ad is a future of advertising.   Text, Video, Audio - it doesn't matter. The platform is important. All social networks can be divided into two segments – communication oriented (Facebook, Instagram,...) and content oriented (YouTube, Twitch, …). Communication oriented networks are mostly used for communication among friends. Such social networks camouflage advertising in posts and are not interested in supporting blogger’s activity which leads to an obvious limitation for bloggers and advertising with them. For instance, Facebook does not allow having more than 5000 friends. Instagram bans links to external sources.  Content oriented networks are normally used for unique content. The main instrument for accessing the content is subscription to particular bloggers but this way requires following the social network’s instructions. Special competences and resources are necessary to generate high quality content. Being a part of such networks becomes a regular job for popular creators (bloggers). Normally, there is a high volume of content and the user needs time to check every post, so the network integrates advertising into this content. Such social networks cannot exist without bloggers. Therefore they are interested in opinion leaders’ development. It is useless for content oriented (Youtube, Twitch and so on) networks to fight p2p advertising. Any kind of pressure exerted on bloggers harms the audience. In such situation, content oriented networks can’t do anything to decrease p2p advertising market. So Youtube as the biggest content-oriented social network is our priority. Instagram, Facebook and others are not

Title: 🔥[ANN][Live ICO] 🔥Efir.io - P2P “AdWords” for native advertising with bloggers
Body: Everyone has a smartphone. Samsung, Apple, Xiaomi, and so on. All of them could make a call, send a message, open a browser or take a photo. But why someone buys Samsung, but others buy Apple? Is it because of the difference between the camera megapixels? Do we really feel the difference between new and old processor? We buy Apple or Samsung because the brand makes us feel better, happier, more successful. Smartphone  itself does nothing. PR - is a technology, that builds  a positive associations to the brand in your head. From day to day popular brands tells us to be better with them thousand times. And we believe. How does the PR specialist measure the PR outcome? Only by the reach. But we know how to measure the PR quality. PR Quality assessment will be a paid oracle for a smart-contract deal between blogger and advertiser. So this service, as all the other ones will increase the token value.

Proposal will consist of slides with agency identity and agency contact details. One slide per each blogger. Slides will give bloggers’ public and nonpublic analytics, for example, number of views per last ten videos, age and gender structure of the audience, overall price, cost per 1 view and so on. Agency should just add a slide about its client and in a couple of minutes send a Letter of Proposal. And It really works right now. We are planning to automate the hole business process of agency from the LOP to the final reports. It’s paid service. So every agency using it will increase the token value.

Title: 🔥[ANN][Live ICO] 🔥Efir.io - P2P “AdWords” for native advertising with bloggers
Body: Blogger is an ordinary human, who likes to share interesting information with the audience. What competencies should a blogger have to become a professional? Blogger has to be a cameraman, sound director, video editor, screenwriter, graphic designer and so on at the same time. We know 8 main and 40 secondary competencies of the professional blogger.  We gather media market specialists to professional associations and make the blogger go through this associations. First stage is bloggers assessment. As a result we get a professional team consisting of a blogger and a market media specialist. Specialists could teach the blogger or get employed as a part of the team. When the blogger’s team is formed, venture investor could buy the blogger’s rights for future advertisement placements.  Third stage - bloggers development. Collected funds are used by blogger’s team to develop. It leads to rising of the content quality, audience growth and increase in blogger’s advertising cost. So the advertising rights held by investor become more expensive. The last stage - to sell advertising rights using efir.io. So every deal on decentralized production will increase the token value.

Title: 🔥[ANN][Live ICO] 🔥Efir.io - P2P “AdWords” for native advertising with bloggers

So we started this project to increase bloggers advertising quality and to fix the lack of bloggers in some thematic niches. This project use our token and will sell services at efir.io marketplace.  Second project at our marketplace is services for agencies. Right now, agencies from Russia could enter the service, search for bloggers, set an agency commission, press only one button and in ten seconds download a powerpoint business proposal for an advertiser. We are planning to automate the hole business process of agency from the LOP to the final reports. It’s paid service. So every agency using it should increase the token value.   The third project at our marketplace is analytics. We monitor trends all over the world and we could quickly answer a lot of complex questions. For example, we could compare competing brands by their popularity in different regions. What is more popular Coke or Pepsi, BMW or Mercedes, Apple or Samsung?   The fourth project is PR quality assessment. We measure the emotional influence of bloggers advertising video to measure the PR outcome. It’s a paid oracle in a deal between blogger and advertiser.

After the Token Exchange all credits will be summarized and cryptocurrency will be paid to all participants according to their credits. Author: qaazqaaz
Title: 🔥[ANN][Live ICO] 🔥Efir.io - P2P “AdWords” for native advertising with bloggers
Body: Thx for a good question. Yes we focus only on bloggers. Bloggers focus gives us an opportunity to make the best bloggers platform.  Blogger is a specialist. Platform doesn't matter. It could be text, audio or video content-platform. But not all social nets allow p2p advertising. Social networks are not interested in developing p2p advertising market as advertiser’s money goes directly to bloggers leaving out the social nets. Some Social networks have an opportunity to fight p2p market, but others can’t do anything. All social networks can be divided into two segments – communication oriented (Facebook, Instagram,...) and content oriented (YouTube, Twitch, Youku…). Communication oriented networks are mostly used for communication among friends. Such social networks camouflage advertising in posts and are not interested in supporting blogger’s activity which leads to an obvious limitation for bloggers and advertising with them. For instance, Facebook does not allow having more than 5000 friends. Instagram bans links to external sources. Content oriented networks are normally used for unique content. The main instrument for accessing the content is subscription to particular bloggers but this way requires following the social network’s instructions. Special competences and resources are necessary to generate high quality content. Being a part of such networks becomes a regular job for popular creators (bloggers). Normally, there is a high volume of content and the user needs time to check every post, so the network integrates advertising into this content. Such social networks cannot exist without bloggers. Therefore they are interested in opinion leaders’ development. It is useless for content oriented (Youtube, Twitch and so on) networks to fight p2p advertising. Any kind of pressure exerted on bloggers harms the audience. In such situation, content oriented networks can’t do anything to decrease p2p advertising market. So Youtube as the biggest content-oriented social network is our priority. Instagram, Facebook and others are not.
